                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d595">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Powell</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Part au Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-05-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 15, 1902</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Powell reports that a committee of eleven, with ex-President Canal as
                    chairman, has been named to conduct affairs at Port au Prince, and that a
                    similar committee has been named in all cities of the Republic; that the admiral
                    in command of naval vessels is to leave for the north, and that all is
                    quiet.)</p>
            </div>
